is just equal to 1.

00:10:04.040 --> 00:10:07.460
So the Laplace transform of
our shifted delta function

00:10:07.460 --> 00:10:13.060
times some other function is
equal to e to the minus sc

00:10:13.060 --> 00:10:15.200
times f of c.

00:10:15.200 --> 00:10:18.160
Let me write that
again down here.

00:10:18.160 --> 00:10:20.650
Let me write it all at once.

00:10:20.650 --> 00:10:25.590
So the Laplace transform of our
shifted delta function t

00:10:25.590 --> 00:10:32.900
minus c times some function
f of t, it equals e

00:10:32.900 --> 00:10:35.570
to the minus c.

00:10:35.570 --> 00:10:38.420
Essentially, we're just
evaluating e to the minus st

00:10:38.420 --> 00:10:39.240
evaluated at c.

00:10:39.240 --> 00:10:44.110
So e to the minus
cs times f of c.

00:10:44.110 --> 00:10:47.420
We're essentially just
evaluating these things at c.

00:10:47.420 --> 00:10:48.680
This is what it equals.

00:10:48.680 --> 00:10:51.160
So from this we can get a lot
of interesting things.

00:10:51.160 --> 00:10:55.080
What is the Laplace transform--
actually, what is

